### Handling Worker Messages for UI Updates

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/docs/source/tutorials/next.md

Defines the `onMessageReceived` function to process messages from the Transformers.js worker. It uses a switch statement to update the `ready` and `result` state variables based on the status ('initiate', 'ready', 'complete') and output from the worker.

```js
const onMessageReceived = (e) => {
  switch (e.data.status) {
    case 'initiate':
      setReady(false);
      break;
    case 'ready':
      setReady(true);
      break;
    case 'complete':
      setResult(e.data.output[0])
      break;
