### React Progress Display Component

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/docs/source/tutorials/react.md

A simple React component to visually display the download progress of model files. It takes a text label and a percentage value to render a progress bar. No external dependencies are required beyond React.

```jsx
export default function Progress({ text, percentage }) {
  percentage = percentage ?? 0;
  return (
    <div className="progress-container">
      <div className='progress-bar' style={{ 'width': `${percentage}%` }}>
        {text} ({`${percentage.toFixed(2)}%`})
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

